he's paying the penalty
because it's too expensive."

14:32.033 --> 14:36.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, President Obama said,
oh, we want to make insurance
perfect for people, but he added

14:36.600 --> 14:41.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all these regulatory mandates,
made it too expensive. Young,
healthy people didn't buy

14:41.133 --> 14:45.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it, and the people remaining in
the insurance pool were sicker
and sicker. That's the adverse

14:45.766 --> 14:49.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
selection and the death
spiral of Obamacare.

14:49.100 --> 14:54.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so really we do need
to discuss the intricacies
of what worked and what
didn't work in Obamacare.

14:56.100 --> 14:58.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think the better way to
do this is to let individuals
have the freedom to choose

14:58.466 --> 15:02.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what kind of insurance is
best for them. The government
doesn't always know best. Maybe

15:02.833 --> 15:04.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the individual should
be allowed to choose.

15:04.866 --> 15:08.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator, I
hear you, and I have read of
some of the other comments you

15:08.200 --> 15:11.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have made lately. You have
some very strong views on this.
As you just said, you would

15:11.933 --> 15:16.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
like to do away with
this tax on individuals
earning -- high earners.

15:18.833 --> 15:22.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have talked about doing
