about all those?

25:56.033 --> 25:59.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WARREN BUFFETT: Well, you can't
really talk about specifics
without looking at the whole

25:59.733 --> 26:02.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
thing.

26:02.266 --> 26:04.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But if they're talking about
making it revenue-neutral,
you know, I think if
they're going to make

26:04.266 --> 26:08.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it revenue-neutral, it ought to
be -- it ought to be something
other than revenue-neutral

26:10.566 --> 26:14.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the guys like me. Our
rates should go up, allowing
others to go down somewhat.

26:14.466 --> 26:18.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think there ought to be
minimum taxes for people that
make $10 million a year, and a

26:18.833 --> 26:21.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
different one at a million
a year, but certainly
at $10 million a year.

26:21.533 --> 26:26.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: They also, as you
know, want to tackle business
corporate tax rates. They're

26:26.266 --> 26:30.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
talking about the current
corporate rate, lowering it
from 35 percent to 15 percent?

26:30.900 --> 26:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president has talked about
-- I guess Speaker Paul Ryan
this week said 20 percent.

26:37.200 --> 26:39.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What would that
mean for you if...

26:39.733 --> 26:43.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WARREN BUFFETT: Well, it
