food stamps, and it takes away
their incentive to do anything.

27:25.266 --> 27:29.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If a kid comes out of the right
womb in this country, they
have got food stamps for their

27:29.033 --> 27:32.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rest of their life. They just
call them stocks and bonds. And
their welfare officer is their

27:32.800 --> 27:35.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
trust officer.

27:35.333 --> 27:38.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, I think I -- I
think having a significant
estate tax that starts
at a fair-sized level

27:41.300 --> 27:46.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is -- if you're going to have
to raise $3.5 trillion, I
think that's a good source of

27:46.066 --> 27:49.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
revenue, and that I -- it
shouldn't apply to, you know,
99 percent of the people.

27:49.866 --> 27:54.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You have been
very -- I mean, very open about
your own taxes, and people

27:54.500 --> 27:57.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
